	 Sehwags was the 22nd 300-plus score in Tests and the third versus South Africa         
	 Sehwag has scored the fastest triple century in Tests in terms of balls faced. His 300 came in 278 balls. Matthew Haydens was the previous fastest and had taken 362 balls versus Zimbabwe in 2003         
	 Sehwag became only the third player in Tests to score two triple hundreds, the others being Sir Don Bradman and Brian Lara. He is the only player to score two triple hundreds one at home and one away. Bradmans triples came away from home and Lara scored both at home                                                                                                                             
